          <label id="Question.Label.R7">R7. Problems with adult relationships</label>
          <help-text id="Question.Help.R7">Answer based upon current status of adult relationships in the household:&lt;br/&gt;a. Answer 'none applicable' if the question does not apply or there are no problems observed.&lt;br/&gt;b. Answer 'Yes', if adult relationships in the household are harmful/disruptive or if domestic violence is present. Harmful/tumultuous relationships have not yet reach the threshold of domestic violence; however, there is evidence of the following:&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt; Child needs are going unmet;&lt;li&gt; The frequency and severity of arguments is increasing; or&lt;li&gt; Adult relationships are becoming progressively more unstable.&lt;/ul&gt;Domestic violence is evidence in a household that has had, since the most recent assessment, physical assault(s) or periods of intimidation/threats/harassment between caregivers or between a caregiver and another adult.</help-text>
        </question>
      </cluster>
